    The main entry point for the Chest Commands API.

    To create a menu, start by looking at Menu.create(Plugin, String, int) and ConfigurableIcon.create(Material).

      • getAPIVersion

        public static int getAPIVersion()
        Returns the API version number, which is increased every time the API changes. This number is used to check if a certain method or class (which may have been added later) is present or not.

        All public API classes and methods are documented with the Javadoc tag @since, indicating in which API version that element was introduced.

        You can use it to require a minimum version, as features may be added (rarely removed) in future versions. The first version of the API is 1.

        Returns:
        the current API version
        Since:
        1

      • registerPlaceholder

        public static void registerPlaceholder(@NotNull
                                       @NotNull Plugin plugin,
                                       @NotNull
                                       @NotNull String identifier,
                                       @NotNull
                                       @NotNull PlaceholderReplacer placeholderReplacer)
        Registers a placeholder that will be replaced by a custom value provided by the given placeholder replacer, which may be different for each player.

        Placeholders can be used in some parts of ConfigurableIcon, most notably the name and the lore, but they are disabled by default. The method ConfigurableIcon.setPlaceholdersEnabled(boolean) must be invoked on each icon which should have placeholders enabled.

        Menus loaded by Chest Commands from the menus folder always display placeholders, including those registered through this method.

        The identifier is used to compute which placeholder formats will invoke the replacer callback. For example, given the identifier "test", the callback would be invoked to replace the following placeholders (case insensitive):

        • {test}
        • {test: argument}
        • {pluginName/test}
        • {pluginName/test: argument}
        • {PLUGINNAME/TEST: abc}
        • ...
        The plugin name is used as optional namespace, to distinguish two placeholders with the same identifier but registered by distinct plugins.

        This method replaces any currently registered placeholder with the same plugin and identifier (case insensitive).

        Parameters:
        plugin - the plugin registering the placeholder
        identifier - the case-insensitive identifier of the placeholder, which can only contain letters, digits and underscores; its length must be between 1 and 30 characters
        placeholderReplacer - the callback that returns the displayed value
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the identifier contains invalid characters, is too short or too long
        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        PlaceholderReplacer.getReplacement(Player, String)

        public static boolean openInternalMenu(@NotNull
